-- Saudi Arabia’s Umrah Visitors Reach 6 Million, Eqtisadiah Says
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-07-25T09:35:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/saudi-arabia-s-umrah-visitors-reach-6-million-eqtisadiah-says.html
Saudi Arabia  said 6 million Muslims
have visited the country to perform rituals since the start of
this Islamic year’s Umrah season,  al-Eqtisadiah  reported, citing
Minister of Hajj Bandar al-Hajjar.  The umrah season started on the first day of the second
Islamic month and will end on the 15th day of the 10th Islamic
month, a period that falls between last Dec. 26 and the coming
Sept. 2, according to the Ministry of Hajj.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Manama   wmahdi@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
